 an illustration of how taking mobility as a starting point fundamentally alters our understanding of subjectivity, politics, and social life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCosmopolitanism. 0aEmigration and immigrationxPsychological aspects. 0aEmigration and immigrationxSocial aspects. 0aImmigrantsxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478552540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804785525423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804785525.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles